<% content_for :header do %>
  <h1>Factlink on your site</h1>
<% end %>

<% content_for :title do %>
  Factlink &mdash; On your site
<% end %>

<% content_for :content do %>
  <%= image_tag('static/add-factlink.png', class: 'on-your-site-image') %>
  <h1>Empower your visitors</h1>
  <p>Give people more control over the content on your website. Let your visitors discuss about specific statements within your page. Factlink is a powerful tool to determine the reliability of the sources you aggregate. Using Factlink will not only generate more traffic to your website but also increases your authority on the subjects your writing about.</p>

  <h4>Installing Factlink in WordPress</h4>
  <p>If you own a WordPress website manual implementation is not required. Just download and install the <%= link_to 'WordPress plugin', 'http://wordpress.org/plugins/factlink/'%>. You can annotate any statement on your website by selecting the statement and clicking the add Factlink button. The WordPress plugin includes the same functionality as the manual install.
  </p>
  <%= link_to 'Get WordPress plugin', 'http://wordpress.org/plugins/factlink/', class: 'button button-confirm' %>

  <h4>Installing Factlink manually</h4>
  <p>Factlink features can manually be integrated in your website. Add the following string of code above the closing <code>&lt;/body&gt;</code> tag:</p>
  <code class="code-line">
    &lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;https://static.factlink.com/lib/dist/factlink_loader_publishers.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
  </code>
<% end %>
